{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/swiftonig.SwiftOnig\/documentation\/SwiftOnig\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Getting Started","modules":[{"name":"SwiftOnig"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/swiftonig.SwiftOnig\/documentation\/SwiftOnig"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to integrate SwiftOnig into your project and perform your first regular expression match.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftonig\/gettingstarted"]}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Essentials","title":"Essentials","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/swiftonig.SwiftOnig\/documentation\/SwiftOnig\/Introduction","doc:\/\/swiftonig.SwiftOnig\/documentation\/SwiftOnig\/AdvancedEncodings"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Installation","level":2,"text":"Installation","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add SwiftOnig as a dependency in your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/maogm12\/SwiftOnig\", from: \"0.3.0\")","]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Common-Path","level":2,"text":"Common Path","type":"heading"},{"anchor":"1-Create-a-Regex","level":3,"text":"1. Create a Regex","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a compiled regular expression object. Compilation is synchronous, while automatic runtime initialization still happens internally.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let pattern = #\"\\d+\"#","let regex = try Regex(pattern: pattern)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"2-Perform-a-Match","level":3,"text":"2. Perform a Match","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the string-native "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"firstMatch(of:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method to find the first occurrence of the pattern in a string."}]},{"code":["let input = \"The price is 42 dollars.\"","if let match = try input.firstMatch(of: regex) {","    print(\"Matched: \\(match.substring)\") \/\/ \"42\"","    print(\"Range in input: \\(match.range)\")","}","","let hasMatch = try input.contains(regex)","let matches = try input.matches(of: regex)","let ranges = try input.ranges(of: regex)","let replaced = try input.replacing(regex, with: \"#\")","let parts = try input.split(separator: regex)","let trimmed = try input.trimmingPrefix(regex)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Advanced-Paths","level":2,"text":"Advanced Paths","type":"heading"},{"anchor":"Optional-Runtime-Prewarming","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Optional Runtime Prewarming"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftOnig initializes itself automatically on first use, so no manual setup is required for normal usage.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your application wants to prewarm specific encodings during startup, you can do that explicitly through ","type":"text"},{"code":"Oniguruma.initialize(encodings:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["import SwiftOnig","","try SwiftOnig.Oniguruma.initialize(encodings: [.utf8])"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Runtime-Teardown","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Runtime Teardown"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Most applications do not need to call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Oniguruma.uninitialize()"},{"type":"text","text":". It is an advanced lifecycle API for cases where you explicitly want to tear down the shared runtime, and previously created regex objects must not be reused after that point."}]},{"anchor":"Non-UTF-Byte-Encodings","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Non-UTF Byte Encodings"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your input is already stored in a specific byte encoding, compile the regex with that encoding and search the bytes directly.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let gbBytes: [UInt8] = [196, 227, 186, 195] \/\/ \"你好\" in GB18030","let regex = try Regex(patternBytes: gbBytes, encoding: .gb18030)","let region = try regex.firstMatch(in: gbBytes)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"UTF-16-Input-Performance","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"UTF-16 Input Performance"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using a UTF-16 encoded regex, "},{"code":"String","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Substring","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"String.UTF16View","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"Substring.UTF16View","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" may require temporary UTF-16 materialization for each call."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If repeated UTF-16 searches are performance-sensitive, prepare raw UTF-16 bytes once:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let patternData = Array(\"你好\".utf16).withUnsafeBufferPointer { Data(buffer: $0) }","let regex = try Regex(patternBytes: patternData, encoding: .utf16LittleEndian)","","let preparedInput = Array(\"Hello, 你好!\".utf16).withUnsafeBufferPointer { Data(buffer: $0) }","let region = try regex.firstMatch(in: preparedInput)"]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://swiftonig.SwiftOnig/documentation/SwiftOnig":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftonig.SwiftOnig\/documentation\/SwiftOnig","title":"SwiftOnig","url":"\/documentation\/swiftonig","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A modern Swift wrapper for the Oniguruma regular expression library.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://swiftonig.SwiftOnig/documentation/SwiftOnig/AdvancedEncodings":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftonig.SwiftOnig\/documentation\/SwiftOnig\/AdvancedEncodings","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Encoding"},{"type":"text","text":" directly when your application already owns byte-oriented text data and wants precise control over how SwiftOnig interprets those bytes."}],"kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftonig\/advancedencodings","type":"topic","title":"Advanced Encodings"},"doc://swiftonig.SwiftOnig/documentation/SwiftOnig/Introduction":{"type":"topic","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftOnig is a modern, high-performance regular expression library for Swift, built as a wrapper around the powerful "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kkos\/oniguruma","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" C library."}],"title":"Introduction","url":"\/documentation\/swiftonig\/introduction","identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftonig.SwiftOnig\/documentation\/SwiftOnig\/Introduction","kind":"article"},"https://github.com/kkos/oniguruma":{"title":"Oniguruma","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/kkos\/oniguruma","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kkos\/oniguruma","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Oniguruma","type":"text"}]}}}